{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, future works may be to find appropriate methodologies that may be examined to automate the search phase beyond PubMed or RCTs.",
    "Moving on to the abstract and screening stage, most studies deployed as tools use active learning.",
    "Recapitulating the main associated challenges aside from the use of LLMs and domain knowledge integration, is finding the apt threshold for a reviewer to stop screening.",
    "Only two studies under active learning-related studies have sought to address this.",
    "This, therefore, opens an exploration of further advanced statistical approaches to solve this issue, providing a user with the threshold at which screening can be stopped."
  ]
}